The BMI value of at least 25 indicates that a person is overweight and people with BMI over 30 are considered obese.
You can calculate your BMI by accessing: 1.usa.gov/1D0ZqDv.
For the new study, researchers at the General Min-Sheng Hospital in Taiwan used data tight after 2007 in a trial comparing two types of bariatric surgery - gastric bypass and gastrectomy in manchon - in the medical treatment of type 2 diabetes in people with mild obesity.
The mean BMI in those who underwent surgery decreased from 31 to 24.5 to the end of the fifth year in the study.
In the meantime, BMI in people who received non-surgical treatment against diabetes has remained close to the same level, i.e. 29.
Of those who had surgery, diabetes was completely cured by 36% and partly by 28%.
In the medically treated group, by comparison, diabetes has been completely cured at only 1% and partly at only 2% of subjects.
